<root><template><title>RV</title><part><name>type</name>=<value>command

</value></part><part><name index="1"/><value> ofp

</value></part><part><name index="2"/><value>1.00

</value></part><part><name>gr1</name>=<value> Math

</value></part><part><name index="3"/><value> Returns square root of x.

</value></part><part><name index="4"/><value> '''sqrt''' x

</value></part><part><name>p1</name>=<value> x: [[Number]]

</value></part><part><name index="5"/><value> [[Number]]
		  
</value></part><part><name>x1</name>=<value> <code>[[private]] _squareRoot = sqrt 9;  <template><title>cc</title><part><name index="1"/><value>returns 3</value></part></template></code>

</value></part><part><name index="6"/><value>  [[Math Commands]] [[a_%5E_b|a ^ b]]
</value></part></template>

<dl class="command_description">
<comment><!-- Note Section BEGIN -->
</comment>
<dd class="notedate">Posted on 18:05, 24 August 2014 (EST)</dd>
<dt class="note">[[User:Benargee|Benargee]]<dd class="note">
Alternatively use "x^0.5" or "x^(1/2)". <code>_sq = 9^0.5;  //Result is 3
_sq = 9^(1/2);  //Result is 3</code>
You can use this method to get any root.
Cubed root = x^(1/3) or x^0.333[repeating].
Root 4 = x^(1/4) or x^0.25.


<comment><!-- Note Section END -->
</comment></dl>
